06-05|language=Turkish}}</ref> The Chief Public Prosecutor of the Supreme Court of Appeals initially used \"AKP\", but after an objection from the party,<ref>Ebru Toktar and Ersin Bal. [http://www.tumgazeteler.com/?a=2820893 \"Laiklik anlay\u0131\u015flar\u0131m\u0131z farkl\u0131\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110512070628/http://www.tumgazeteler.com/?a=2820893|date=2011-05-12}} {{in lang|tr}}. ''Ak\u015fam'', 2008-05-07.</ref> \"AKP\" was replaced with \"Adalet ve Kalk\u0131nma Partisi\" (without abbreviation) in documents.\n{{Refend}}\n\n== Literature ==\n* {{cite journal |first=\u00dcmit (ed.) |last=Cizre |title=Secular and Islamic politics in Turkey: The making of the Justice and Development Party |publisher=Routledge |year=2008}}\n* {{cite journal |first=\u00dcmit |last=Cizre |title=A New Politics of Engagement: The Turkish Military, Society and the AKP |journal=Democracy, Islam, and Secularism in Turkey |year=2012}}\n* {{cite journal |first1=William |last1=Hale |first2=Ergun |last2=\u00d6zbudun |title=Islamism, Democracy and Liberalism in Turkey: The Case of the AKP |publisher=Routledge |year=2010}}\n* {{cite journal |first=M. Hakan (ed.) |last=Yavuz |title=The Emergence of a New Turkey: Islam, Democracy and the AK Parti |publisher=The University of Utah Press |year=2006}}\n* {{cite journal |first=M. Hakan |last=Yavuz |title=Secularism and Muslim Democracy in Turkey |publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=2009}}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Gezi Park protests]]\n* [[2013 corruption scandal in Turkey]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Justice and Development Party (Turkey)|Justice and Development Party}}\n*{{Official website|http://www.akparti.org.tr/en}} {{in lang|en|tr}}\n*[http://www.akgenclik.org.tr/ AK Youth] {{in lang|tr}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20150629061751/http://www.siyasetakademisi.org/ AKP Political Academy] {{in lang|tr}}\n*[http://www.akkanal.com/ AK Kanal] {{in lang|tr}}\