{"title_page": "Courrier d'Avignon", "text_new": "{{short description|Periodical literature}}\n{{italic title}}\n{{Expand French|date=July 2010|Courrier d'Avignon}}\nThe '''''Courrier d'Avignon''''' was a newspaper which had an important role in the international French-language press of the 18th century. Published in the [[Avignon|papal enclave]] within the kingdom of France, then in [[Monaco]], it escaped the system controlling the press within France itself (privilege with permission) despite being under papal control. It appeared from 1733 to 1793 with two breaks, the first between July 1768 and August 1769 due to [[Avignon]]'s annexation by France and the second between 30 November 1790 and 24 May 1791.\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Publications established in 1733]]\n[[Category:Publications disestablished in 1793]]\n[[Category:Media in Avignon]]\n[[Category:Defunct newspapers of France]]\n[[Category:Newspapers of the French Revolution]]\n[[Category:Media in Monaco]]\n\n\n{{france-newspaper-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Periodical literature}}\n{{italic title}}\n{{Expand French|date=July 2010|Courrier d'Avignon}}\nThe '''''Courrier d'Avignon''''' was a newspaper which had an important role in the international French-language press of the 18th century. Published in the [[Avignon|papal enclave]] within the kingdom of France, then in [[Monaco]], it escaped the system controlling the press within France itself (privilege with permission) despite being under papal control. It appeared from 1733 to 1793 with two breaks, the first between July 1768 and August 1769 due to [[Avignon]]'s annexation by France and the second between 30 November 1790 and 24 May 1791.\n{{Authority control}}\n[[Category:Publications established in 1733]]\n[[Category:Publications disestablished in 1793]]\n[[Category:Media in Avignon]]\n[[Category:Defunct newspapers of France]]\n[[Category:Newspapers of the French Revolution]]\n[[Category:Media in Monaco]]\n[[Category:French-language newspapers]]\n\n\n{{france-newspaper-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Hmains", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:category refine, sort sequence", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Courrier_d%27Avignon"}
